{"type":"text","timestamp":1778468509913,"sessionID":"ses_1eb095841ffeI7PjslP58h1Hev","part":{"id":"prt_e14fb79c80013Bg9d2rlLmFw5U","messageID":"msg_e14fb29b1001hufW7YAF6HdQW6","sessionID":"ses_1eb095841ffeI7PjslP58h1Hev","type":"text","text":"The task is complete. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n1. **Analyzed the issue**: The request was to obsolete GO:0009095 (aromatic amino acid biosynthetic process, prephenate pathway) because it is a pre-composed MetaCyc superpathway that combines two separate pathways already represented in GO.\n2. **Pre-validated**: Ran `robot convert` on `src/ontology/go-edit.obo` — passed without errors.\n3. **Searched for usages**: Confirmed via `obo-grep.pl` that GO:0009095 only appears in its own stanza, so no rewiring of other terms was needed.\n4. **Performed the obsoletion** using `obo-checkout.pl`, edited `terms/GO_0009095.obo`, and checked it back in with `obo-checkin.pl`:\n   - Removed `is_a`, all `intersection_of`, `synonym`, and `xref` tags\n   - Prefixed name with `obsolete ` and definition with `OBSOLETE.`\n   - Added a `comment` explaining the reason\n   - Added `is_obsolete: true`\n   - Added two `consider` terms (`GO:0009094` and `GO:0006571`)\n   - Updated `term_tracker_item` to point to issue #32005\n5. **Post-validated**: Both `robot convert` and `robot reason -r ELK` passed successfully.\n6. **Committed** the change to `src/ontology/go-edit.obo` with a detailed message.\n7. **Created** `ISSUE_COMMENTS.md` and `PR_COMMENTS.md` in the repository root.","time":{"start":1778468485576,"end":1778468509911}}}
